 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/uquasimo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quasimo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Patriarch - DoAC</span><br>  Posts: 1576<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(1/15/02 3:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Grouping</span><hr size=1> Thank you for bringing this up Seerpent.<br>
<br>
This is something that has become an issue of late.  When your in a group of non-sh, when do you say &quot;thanks, going to party with my guild&quot; and when don't you?  It's often something that leaves you in a no-win situation.  In times like these go with your heart.  If your in a good group somewhere, then by all means.. we encourage you to befriend non-hawks and it's for the good of the realm.  If your in a crappy group going nowwhere, then there's your excuse!  Politely tell them duty calls!  and come join the fun.<br>
<br>
There is the other side of the coin here.  What do you do when a silver hawk is in a group somewhere and you've nothing to do?  If you are of appropriate lvl, then it's quite alright to see if there is a spot for you, and many times there is.  But if you are not, don't expect<br>
<br>
I think people need to come to terms with something.  There WILL be nights when you log in to play and you just don't get into a group... silver hawk or otherwise.  It just happens, at least it happens to everyone I know, including me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I am pleased with how often I have been able to get into a great group though, and I appreciate it when that happens.   Everyone has to develop their own mechanisms to deal with the game when that great group isn't there and waiting for you though.<br>
<br>
Here are some things to try:<br>
<br>
Quests<br>
Crafts<br>
Helping other people (healers are very welcome at the parth farm for example)<br>
Playing an alt<br>
Solo (if you can, I know I don't do well with this one)<br>
Start your own group!  do a /who &lt;class&gt; level and see if anyone that would be good to hunt with comes up (pay attention to what zone they are in when you do this though.. someone that is in a dungeon most likely has a group).  Politely give them a tell and don't expect to find someone... you might be pleasantly surprised.  It also helps to go from zone to zone and check the LFG flags.<br>
<br>
If all else fails, then take a night off and enjoy a good movie or something (what!  RL... are you crazy Quasimo!?) hehe.<br>
<br>
At any rate, Seerpent brings up a great point.  It would be great to group with EVERY hawk all the time.  I know I would love that, but it's just not possible.  If someone is to<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  low or to high</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a level for a group, then your endangering the groups play time as well as your own. <p>Silver Hawks Forever,</br>
